o>-</mo></math>region and the negative terminal to the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo></math>region of the diode.</p><p>The potential of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>-</mo></math>side is more positive that of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo></math>side, hence diode is in forward biasing. In&nbsp;forward biasing it acts as short&nbsp;circuit, hence&nbsp;current flows.</p><p>In case of forward biased&nbsp;circuit P-junction should be at higher potential.&nbsp;<br /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/Q_28_AnsExp_1.jpg\" style=\"width: 311px; height: 63px;\" /></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ09220867", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61bb8219f4390170f33796c2", "61602457307cfc9adff9a7fb", "6160245b478a3fc1b68a77b1", "6160245904d4c5ba91160e33", "6160245a6cba32b9f037a1f9", "61c08999c3044bf5a42ce2d9", "61964c9755b28533946a8516", "61e7bd76457232a5c257f2e5", "61964c989d521687020e0bf6", "629109f1cfc566d78232fe43", "62962124eb57a59a83a5151c", "629f3a935465153c88ad566a", "629f390e23a8566a6252b361", "64eb06c73118f713ecfef0be", "66d58536a75f05ee8564f542", "67921d611d5b5072da5e9a94", "67fdff47378e1624ea7b698b", "680920333a10446a207fdf4c"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f483